header.gameNote: SOUTHERN CONFERENCE MEN'S CHAMPIONSHIP - QUARTERFINALS AT CHATTANOOGA TN

article.headline: Coll. of Charleston 78, Elon 60
article.story: CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. -- Andrew Goudelock scored 25 points as College of Charleston defeated Elon 78-60 on Saturday night to advance to the Southern Conference tournament semifinals for the fifth consecutive year. The Cougars, who will face Furman on Sunday, are the only league team to reach five consecutive semifinals, but have not won the tournament since 1999. College of Charleston (23-9) made 17 of 29 first-half shots (58.6 percent) to take a 43-22 halftime lead. The Cougars also made 5 of 10 first-half 3-pointers. A reverse layup by Trent Wiedeman at the 17:43 mark made it 7-0, and a Wiedeman tip-in with 13:47 left provided the first double-digit lead at 16-6. Wiedeman added 20 points and Donavan Monroe 14 for the Cougars. Drew Spradlin scored 13 to lead the Phoenix (14-17), who pulled to 54-42 midway through the second half before the Cougars countered with seven straight points.
